---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Viewing, Editing & Previewing Files — URDF Format & Model Description"
  description="Open URDF in VS Code, install the URDF Visualizer and XML extensions, and preview the model directly. Then use the write-a-bit, preview, edit, preview-again loop to gradually nudge the model into the right position, orientation, and proportion."
  lang="en"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container urdf-preview">
      <a class="back-link" href="/">&larr; Back to Home</a>

      <header class="detail-header">
        <h1 class="detail-title">Opening It Up: How to Check and Edit URDF</h1>
        <p class="detail-subtitle">
          By now we've already met URDF and seen its most basic structure and example. Naturally, the next question is: once the file is written, <strong>how do you know whether you got it right?</strong> If you only stare at the XML text, it's actually quite hard to immediately spot where the model is crooked, where parts are wrongly connected, or where a part is sized unreasonably. So the focus here is simple: open the URDF, edit it if needed, and preview the model.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="callout-card">
        <p class="callout-text">
          We won't take the ROS 2 route here — instead, we'll use a lighter approach. With just <strong>VS Code</strong> and a URDF preview extension, you can already see what the model looks like, whether parts are connected correctly, and whether the positions are off. This fits the current stage well, and it connects naturally with the VS Code editing flow you've been using.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: Where files live -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Where Do URDF Files Usually Live?</h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        URDF is essentially a text file, so you can put it in your own project folder. Many people set up a separate folder called <code>urdf</code> just for model files; if there are also 3D models or textures, they'll often go into separate <code>meshes</code> and <code>textures</code> folders. You can organize it like this:
      </p>

      <pre class="code-block code-block--tree"><code>my_robot/
├─ urdf/
│   └─ my_robot.urdf
├─ meshes/
└─ textures/</code></pre>

      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        If you're heading toward <strong>ROS 2</strong> later, you'll often see URDF placed inside a package's urdf folder. But at this stage, there's no need to be tied to ROS 2's folder structure first — just keep the model file and its resources in the same project, and that's enough.
      </p>

      <!-- Section: What tool -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">What Tool to Open and Edit With?</h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        The most convenient approach is to use <strong>VS Code</strong>. Since URDF is just an XML text file, any text editor can technically modify it. But VS Code makes it look much clearer: tags are easier to distinguish, and your eyes won't get lost while editing.
      </p>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        Once the file is open, the things you'll typically end up editing are:
      </p>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li>Dimensions — like length, radius, height</li>
        <li>Color or appearance</li>
        <li>The position of <code>origin</code></li>
        <li>The type, axis, and connection style of <code>joint</code></li>
      </ul>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        After editing, save the file. The next step isn't to keep staring at the text — it's to <strong>preview the result</strong>.
      </p>

      <!-- Section: VS Code extensions -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Recommended VS Code Extensions</h2>

      <div class="ext-grid">
        <article class="ext-card">
          <p class="ext-tag">Main tool</p>
          <h3 class="ext-title">URDF Visualizer</h3>
          <p class="ext-desc">
            This is the main tool for previewing URDF. It can display the model directly inside VS Code, so you can see results without first jumping into ROS 2.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="ext-card">
          <p class="ext-tag">Helper tool</p>
          <h3 class="ext-title">XML</h3>
          <p class="ext-desc">
            This one isn't for viewing 3D — it makes editing URDF more comfortable. Since URDF is XML at heart, having a tool like this makes the tag structure clearer and reduces the chance of missing an opening or closing tag.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: Operation flow -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">The Workflow</h2>

      <ol class="flow-list">
        <li class="flow-item">
          <span class="flow-num">1</span>
          <div class="flow-body">
            <h3 class="flow-title">Open the whole project folder in VS Code</h3>
            <p class="flow-desc">
              Don't just double-click the <code>.urdf</code> file — open the whole project folder in VS Code instead. That way, if the model uses meshes, textures, or other files, you're less likely to hit "file not found" path errors.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="flow-item">
          <span class="flow-num">2</span>
          <div class="flow-body">
            <h3 class="flow-title">Open the URDF preview</h3>
            <p class="flow-desc">
              In VS Code, there are two common ways to open the preview:
            </p>
            <ul class="check-list check-list--inset">
              <li>Press <kbd class="kbd">Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd class="kbd">Shift</kbd> + <kbd class="kbd">P</kbd> and type <code>URDF Visualizer: Preview URDF/Xacro</code></li>
              <li>Or click the preview button in the file's top-right corner</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="flow-desc">
              Either way works — as long as the URDF or Xacro you're currently looking at is the one you want to preview.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="flow-item">
          <span class="flow-num">3</span>
          <div class="flow-body">
            <h3 class="flow-title">First check whether the model shows up properly</h3>
            <p class="flow-desc">
              When the preview opens, don't immediately dive into the syntax details. Look at the obvious things first:
            </p>
            <ul class="check-list check-list--inset">
              <li>Does the model show up at all?</li>
              <li>Are the part sizes reasonable?</li>
              <li>Are the head, body, wheels, and arms attached in the right places?</li>
              <li>Is everything stacked on top of each other, or floating off somewhere weird?</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="flow-item">
          <span class="flow-num">4</span>
          <div class="flow-body">
            <h3 class="flow-title">If something's off, edit and look again</h3>
            <p class="flow-desc">
              If you find a problem, go back to the URDF and edit it. This process usually isn't a one-shot — it's a loop:
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <div class="cycle-card">
        <p class="cycle-text">
          <span class="cycle-step">Write a bit</span>
          <span class="cycle-arrow">→</span>
          <span class="cycle-step">Preview</span>
          <span class="cycle-arrow">→</span>
          <span class="cycle-step">Edit</span>
          <span class="cycle-arrow">→</span>
          <span class="cycle-step">Preview again</span>
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        This is honestly the most practical way to learn URDF.
      </p>

      <!-- Section: Preview features -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">What Can You Do in the Preview?</h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        Tools like URDF Visualizer aren't just for "looking at the picture." According to the official docs, it supports view manipulation and can directly start previewing URDF / Xacro; you can also do joint control by dragging with the mouse, and use measurement tools to inspect coordinates, distances, angles, or areas. So while previewing, pay attention to these:
      </p>

      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li class="feature-item">
          <h3 class="feature-title">Rotate the view</h3>
          <p class="feature-desc">Looking fine from the front doesn't mean the side view is also fine.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="feature-item">
          <h3 class="feature-title">Check link / joint names</h3>
          <p class="feature-desc">Confirm whether each part is really the one you think it is.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="feature-item">
          <h3 class="feature-title">Try dragging joints</h3>
          <p class="feature-desc">If the model has movable joints, watch whether they rotate as expected.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="feature-item">
          <h3 class="feature-title">Read coordinates or measure</h3>
          <p class="feature-desc">Sometimes the position is just slightly off — invisible by eye, but obvious once you measure.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Section: What to check after modifying -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">What's Most Worth Checking After Editing</h2>

      <div class="check-grid">
        <article class="check-card">
          <p class="check-card__step">1</p>
          <h3 class="check-card__title">Is the position right?</h3>
          <p class="check-card__desc">
            This usually has a lot to do with <code>origin</code>. If <code>origin</code> isn't set up properly, the most common result is parts all stacked together — or a part that should sit beside another ending up in the model's center.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="check-card">
          <p class="check-card__step">2</p>
          <h3 class="check-card__title">Is the orientation right?</h3>
          <p class="check-card__desc">
            Some models look attached, but the <code>joint</code> direction is wrong — so an arm rotates in some weird direction, or a wheel turns crooked. If the preview tool lets you see coordinate frames or drag joints, this kind of issue usually surfaces quickly.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="check-card">
          <p class="check-card__step">3</p>
          <h3 class="check-card__title">Is the scale right?</h3>
          <p class="check-card__desc">
            This one trips up beginners often. Sometimes adding one extra zero makes a part absurdly huge, or so tiny it's almost invisible. So every time you preview, glance at the overall proportions first — does it look like the robot you imagined?
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: Common mistakes -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Common Beginner Pitfalls</h2>

      <ol class="trap-list">
        <li class="trap-item">
          <span class="trap-num">1</span>
          <div class="trap-body">
            <h3 class="trap-title">Only opening a single .urdf file, not the whole folder</h3>
            <p class="trap-desc">This causes mesh or texture paths to fail — the preview may show only a shell, or nothing at all.</p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="trap-item">
          <span class="trap-num">2</span>
          <div class="trap-body">
            <h3 class="trap-title">Editing the file but forgetting to save</h3>
            <p class="trap-desc">Sounds tiny, but happens all the time. You think you've edited the model — but the preview is still showing the old version.</p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="trap-item">
          <span class="trap-num">3</span>
          <div class="trap-body">
            <h3 class="trap-title">origin not set correctly</h3>
            <p class="trap-desc">The most common result is parts stacked on top of each other — or the head, which should sit on top, ending up inside the body.</p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="trap-item">
          <span class="trap-num">4</span>
          <div class="trap-body">
            <h3 class="trap-title">Wrong joint axis or direction</h3>
            <p class="trap-desc">The model looks fine on the surface, but moves strangely once it starts. Wheels turning sideways, arms folding the wrong way — these usually trace back to the <code>joint</code> direction settings.</p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="trap-item">
          <span class="trap-num">5</span>
          <div class="trap-body">
            <h3 class="trap-title">Accidentally writing dimensions too big or too small</h3>
            <p class="trap-desc">Many values in URDF are read as meters. One stray extra zero can instantly turn the model into something the size of a house.</p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="trap-item">
          <span class="trap-num">6</span>
          <div class="trap-body">
            <h3 class="trap-title">Unclosed XML tags</h3>
            <p class="trap-desc">URDF is XML, so tags like <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;/link&gt;</code> need to match up. One missing character and the whole file may fail to parse. The XML extension really helps here, since it makes the tag structure clearer.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .urdf-preview {
    max-width: 52rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* Header */
  .detail-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-6);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .detail-title {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .detail-subtitle {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .detail-subtitle strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Section headings */
  .detail-heading {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .detail-paragraph {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.9;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .detail-paragraph strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Code block (folder tree) */
  .code-block {
    margin: var(--space-3) 0;
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-8);
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.7;
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    overflow-x: auto;
    white-space: pre;
    color: var(--color-heading);
  }

  .code-block code {
    padding: 0;
    background: none;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-size: inherit;
  }

  .code-block--tree {
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
  }

  /* Inline code */
  :global(.detail-paragraph) code,
  :global(.detail-subtitle) code,
  :global(.check-list) code,
  :global(.callout-text) code,
  :global(.flow-desc) code,
  :global(.check-card__desc) code,
  :global(.trap-desc) code,
  :global(.trap-title) code {
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
    color: var(--color-tag-text);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  }

  /* Keyboard shortcut */
  .kbd {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.05em 0.5em;
    margin: 0 0.1em;
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 0.85em;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-bottom-width: 2px;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  }

  /* Check list */
  .check-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-6);
  }

  .check-list li {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.9;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .check-list li::before {
    content: '\2713';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .check-list--inset {
    margin: var(--space-3) 0 var(--space-3);
  }

  .check-list--inset li {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
  }

  /* Callout card */
  .callout-card {
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-8);
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-8);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
  }

  .callout-text {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.9;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .callout-text strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Extension grid (URDF Visualizer / XML) */
  .ext-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-8);
  }

  .ext-card {
    padding: var(--space-8);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    transition: border-color var(--transition);
  }

  .ext-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .ext-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-3);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .ext-title {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
  }

  .ext-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Flow list (numbered operation steps) */
  .flow-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-4);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .flow-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-8);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    transition: border-color var(--transition);
  }

  .flow-item:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .flow-num {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 2rem;
    height: 2rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .flow-body {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .flow-title {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .flow-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.9;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);
  }

  .flow-desc:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Cycle card (write → preview → edit → preview again) */
  .cycle-card {
    margin: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-6);
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-8);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cycle-text {
    margin: 0;
    display: inline-flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
  }

  .cycle-step {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-4);
    background-color: #fff;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .cycle-arrow {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* Feature list (4 things to watch in preview) */
  .feature-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-8);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .feature-item {
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-6);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    transition: border-color var(--transition);
  }

  .feature-item:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .feature-title {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .feature-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Check-card grid (3 things to verify after modifying) */
  .check-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-8);
  }

  .check-card {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    transition: transform var(--transition);
  }

  .check-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .check-card__step {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 1.75rem;
    height: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .check-card__title {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .check-card__desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Trap list (common beginner mistakes) */
  .trap-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--space-6) 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .trap-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-6);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    transition: background-color var(--transition);
  }

  .trap-item:hover {
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
  }

  .trap-num {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 1.75rem;
    height: 1.75rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .trap-body {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
